<p>I have two tables in Cassandra:</p>  <pre><code>CREATE TABLE table1 (           name text PRIMARY KEY,           grade text,            labid List&lt;int&gt;);  CREATE TABLE table2(           name text PRIMARY KEY,           deptid List&lt;int&gt;             grade text,); </code></pre>  <p>for example: </p>  <pre><code>val result: RDD[String, String, List[Int]] = myFunction(); result.saveToCassandra(keyspace, table1) </code></pre>  <p>It is working fine. but in case of using below line:  </p>  <pre><code>result.saveToCassandra(keyspace, table2) </code></pre>  <p>m getting this type of error : com.datastax.spark.connector.types.TypeConversionException: Cannot convert object test_data of type class java.lang.String to List[AnyRef]</p>  <p>Is there any solution using SomeColumns which satisfy the both tables[we don't know which table will be executed]. eg: </p>  <pre><code>result.saveToCassandra(keyspace, table, SomeColumns(....))? </code></pre>